---
By: James Allen
Locus:
  Page: 52
  Verse: 9
Tags:
  - ''
---
The aphorism, “As a man thinketh in his heart, so he is,” embraces the
whole of man’s being. It is so comprehensive that it reaches out to every
condition and circumstance of life. A man is literally what he thinks. His
character is the sum of his thoughts.
